  <Sequence sap2010:Annotation.AnnotationText="Creates and populates the DataRow with the FXRate details that have to be added in SAP taken from the XElement coming from ECB and the required date.&#xA;&#xA;If in_USDFXRate has a value then a Cross Currency Triangulation is needed. Cross currency triangulation is the process where one currency is converted to another via a third common currency.&#xA;&#xA;For example, the EUR-&gt;PLN and EUR-&gt;USD FXRates can be found in the file dowloaded from ECB but the business also requires USD-&gt;PLN to be posted into SAP so instead of getting data from another central bank, this FXRate can be calculated here using this formula: &#xA;EUR-&gt;PLN rate divided by EUR-&gt;USD rate (e.g. 1 EUR = 4.2740 PLN, 1 EUR = 1.0860 USD, 1 USD = 3. 93554 PLN ( 4.2740 / 1.0860 )" DisplayName="PopulateCurrencyRow" sap:VirtualizedContainerService.HintSize="608,1329" sap2010:WorkflowViewState.IdRef="Sequence_1">
